<img data-lazy-fallback="1" decoding="async" width="372" height="405" class="wp-image-1786220" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/soludo-2.jpg" alt="" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/soludo-2.jpg?width=372&amp;auto_optimize=medium 372w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/soludo-2-276x300.jpg?width=276&amp;auto_optimize=medium 276w" sizes="(max-width: 372px) 100vw, 372px"  /> Gov. Chukwuma Soludo of Anambra on Tuesday condemned recent killings in parts of the state. Soludo was reacting to killings in Okpuno in Awka South Local Government Area and Obosi in Idemili North Local Government Area. The News Agency of Nigeria reports that four youths identified as Onyiebo Okoye, Kenechukwu Okeke, Jude Ebenezar and Obinna Maduka were killed in Okpuno community on Jan.1. The President General of Obosi town, Chief Ike Okolo, was shot dead at a petrol station on Jan. 2. Soludo, who described the killings as cult-related, assured that the culprits would be apprehended and made to face the law. Mr Christian Aburime, Press Secretary to the Governor, reported him as saying that the perpetrators would be apprehended and decisively dealt with, even if they have ran out of town. He said Anambra had enjoyed the best Christmas ever in decades with a new system of traffic control put in place by the government, Anambra Youth Volunteers and the Anambra State Traffic Management Agency. “The governor has condemned the cult-related war among rival groups and subsequent killings in Obosi and Okpuno in Idemili North and Awka South Council Areas. “He assures that the perpetrators will be apprehended and decisively dealt with, even if they have run out of town. He stressed that they will be hunted down to face the full wrath of the law. “The governor further reassured that the cult gangs will surely be tracked down and dealt with decisively in accordance with the law,” he said. Soludo called on the state residents to go about their normal duties and enjoy the season as the challenges were isolated cases which would be nipped in the bud soon.(NAN)  Anambra State Governor, Chukwuma Soludo, has condemned the killing of three members of the Anambra State Vigilante Group. Soludo also reassured Anambra citizens of his resolve to weed out criminal elements in the state at all costs. He made the declaration in a statement made available to newsmen in Awka… In "News" It was a gathering of who’s who at both the palace of the traditional ruler of Obosi Kingdom in Idemili North Local Government Area of Anambra State, Igwe Chidubem Iweka III and the Okpuno Umuota village country home of Hon. Nnamdi Ifebi, Chief of Staff to Chairman, Special Presidential Investigation… In "Just Human" Soludo promises justice for Harira Jubril, slain Adamawa woman, kids In "News"